Purpose
* The purpose of this Law is to:
<\li1>
	* Promote the increase of use of energy from renewable sources to ensure a sustainable development of the Republic of Albania and to comply with its commitments under the Energy Community Treaty;
	* Reduce the import of fossil fuels, greenhouse gas emissions and protect the environment in compliance with the international commitments of the Republic of Albania in line with the relevant international treaties or agreements;
	* Promote the development of the renewable electricity market and its regional integration;
	* Increase the diversification of the energy resources and the security of energy supply in the Republic of Albania;
	* Promote the development of rural and isolated areas by improving their supply with energy.;

This Law establishes:
* The legislative framework for the promotion of use of energy produced from renewable sources;
* The binding national objectives for the contribution of energy from renewable energy sources in gross final energy consumption;
* The rules for supporting the energy produced from renewable sources;
* The obligation for transparency of information;
* The rules for access and operation of the grids for renewable energy sources and connection to the electric energy grid within the territory of the Republic of Albania;
* The rules for issuing, transferring and cancelation of Guarantees of Origin for the energy produced from renewable sources,
* Monitoring the implementation of the reporting requirements and Law.

In this Law the following terms have the following meaning:
* is the energy stored in the form of heat in the ambient air;
* is the energy stored in the form of heat beneath the surface of solid earth;
* is the energy stored in the form of heat in surface water;
* is the biodegradable fraction of products, waste and residues from biological origin from agriculture (including vegetal and animal substances), forestry and related industries including fisheries and aquaculture, as well as the biodegradable fraction of industrial and urban waste;
* â¢Bioliquidsâ¢ are the fuels in liquid or gaseous form, mixed with hydrocarbon fuels, produced from biomass, according to the dispositions on law no. 9876, date 14.2.2008 â¢For the production, transportation, and the trade of biofuels and other renewable fuels to be used on the transport sector.
* means energy from renewable non-fossil sources, namely wind, solar, aerothermal, geothermal, hydrothermal and ocean energy, hydropower, biomass, landfill gas, sewage treatment plant gas and biogases;
* Is the entire amount of energy delivered to the territory of the Republic of Albania , for industrial purposes , transportation , for the household sector , for different services , including public and private services , agriculture , forestry and fisheries , including the consumption of electricity and heat even for subsistence in all energy sectors , as well as loss of electricity and heat in the transmission and distribution system ;
* is an electronic document which has the sole function of providing proof to a final customer that a given share or quantity of energy was produced from renewable sources;

Duties of the Agency responsible for renewable energy sources
* The agency responsible for renewable energy as an institution depending on the Minister shall have the following main duties :
<\li1>
	* Creating, recording and updating the registry of priority energy producers;
	* Registering the energy balance of all priority energy producers;
	* Drafting and submission to the Ministry of the draft of the National Renewable Energy Action Plan in deadlines defined by this ministry;;
	* Monitoring the implementation of the National Renewable Energy Action Plan following the approval by the Council of Ministers;
	* Creates and submits to the Ministry and ERE by the 1st of June of each year an evaluation of the share of energy generated from renewable sources as compared to the gross final consumption of energy for the previous year;

Duties of the Agency responsible for renewable energy sources
* The agency responsible for renewable energy as an institution depending on the Minister shall have the following main duties :
<\li1>
	* Creating, recording and updating the registry of priority energy producers;
	* Registering the energy balance of all priority energy producers;
	* Drafting and submission to the Ministry of the draft of the National Renewable Energy Action Plan in deadlines defined by this ministry;;
	* Monitoring the implementation of the National Renewable Energy Action Plan following the approval by the Council of Ministers;
	* Creates and submits to the Ministry and ERE by the 1st of June of each year an evaluation of the share of energy generated from renewable sources as compared to the gross final consumption of energy for the previous year;
* Developing all required documents and submitting them for approval to the Ministry responsible for energy as provided in Article 6 (1) of this Law;
<\li2>
	* The council of ministers, upon the Ministers proposal appoints or creates an institution that will carry out the duties and responsibilities of the Agency responsible for renewable energy.
<\li1>

The beneficiaries of the operational support under a Contract for Difference and the maximal level of such support will be determined in a competitive process open to all generators producing electricity from renewable energy on the basis of clear, transparent and non-discriminatory criteria, except the cases in which:
* only one or a very limited number of projects could be eligible for a competitive bidding process, or
<\li1>
* a tendering process would lead to demonstrable higher support levels, or
* a tendering process would result in demonstrable lower prices
* The longer-term potential of a given new and innovative technology;
* The need to achieve diversification of resources ;
* Network constraints and grid stability;
* System integration costs;
* The need to avoid distortions on the raw material markets from biomass support.
* of an installed electric energy capacity up to 2 MW;

The support according to the contract for difference do not apply for priority producers
* of an installed electric energy capacity up to 3 MW for wind energy;
* for demonstrative projects;

transmission and distribution system operators shall take into account the technical constraints and economic efficiency of the selected connection point to the grid. The transmission and distribution system operators shall provide any new producer of energy from renewable sources wishing to be connected to the system with the comprehensive and necessary information required, including:
* a comprehensive and detailed estimate of the costs associated with the connection;
* a reasonable and precise timetable for receiving and processing the request for grid connection;
* a reasonable indicative timetable for any proposed grid connection.

One guarantee of origin shall be issued in the standard form for an electricity unit of 1 MWh and it shall specify:
* The energy source from which the energy was produced,
* the start and the end dates of the production;
* The name , location, type and capacity of the installation where the energy was produced;
* Whether and to what extent the producer has benefited from investment support and from other national support schemes;
* Date of commissioning of the installation and when became operational;
* The date, country of issuance of the guarantee and a unique identification number;

ERE shall approve a special regulation on the establishment of an accurate, reliable and fraud-resistant system for issuing, transfer and cancelation of the guarantees of origin. This regulation, among other things, particularly stipulates:
* The documentation to be provided by the producer for the technical qualification of its installation as a plant generating electricity from renewable energy sources;
* The technical qualification procedure, and in particular the time limit for ERE to reply to applications submitted and the legal consequences resulting from failure to comply with this obligation;
* The application procedure for the issuance, registration, transfer or cancellation of guarantees of origin;
* The procedure for monitoring and verification of the accuracy and reliability of the obligations implemented by the producer;
* Matters related to the collaboration with competent authorities of EU Member States and other countries with which an agreement for mutual recognition of guarantees of origin is signed.
